# .dockerignore — shrink the build context sent to the Docker daemon.
#
# The Dockerfile does `COPY . .` into the builder. Without this file the whole
# repo (history, planning notes, coverage artifacts, docs, CI config) is shipped
# into the build context and baked into the builder layer — slow, and it leaks
# non-build material into the image cache.
#
# The build only needs the Go module graph (go.mod/go.sum) and the Go packages
# under cmd/ and internal/. There is no go:embed, so no other tree is required.
# Everything excluded below is verified NOT to be a build input; if a future
# change adds a go:embed of a path listed here, un-ignore that path.

# Version control and local planning notes
.git
.gitignore
.gitleaks.toml
.github
.planning

# Reference material (never a build input; must never enter any layer)
.refs
references
.claude

# Compiled / build output that must not pollute the build context
/ocu-filestored
*.bin
*.coverprofile
cover.out
coverage
testdata/rapid

# Docs and project meta — not compiled into the binary
docs
*.md
LICENSE
LICENSE-APACHE
LICENSE-MIT
NOTICE

# Deploy/runtime assets consumed at deploy time, not at build time
examples
contrib
deploy

# Local instruction files (also untracked, but exclude defensively)
CLAUDE.local.md
